Definition.WordDefinition:
Landlocked \Land"locked`\, a. 1. Inclosed, or nearly inclosed, by land; having no border on the sea; as, a landlocked country. [1913 Webster]
2. (Zo["o]l.) Confined to a fresh-water lake by reason of waterfalls or dams; -- said of fishes that would naturally seek the sea, after spawning; as, the landlocked salmon. [1913 Webster]
landlocked adj : surrounded entirely or almost entirely by land; "a landlocked country"
